Transformers
Topic: Electromagnetism
A transformer is a device which changes the magnitude of an Alternating Current’s voltage. It consists of a primary coil of N_{P} loops of wire and a secondary coil of N_{S} loops. The changing flux due to an Alternating Current voltage in the primary coil induces an AC voltage in the secondary coil. In a theoretical 100% efficient transformer, the ratio of output to input voltages (V_{S}/V_{P}) is equals to the ratio of number of turns N_{S} to N_{P}: \frac{V_{S}}{V_{P}} = \frac{N_{S}}{N_{P}}
The ratio of the Current is in the inverse: \frac{I_{S}}{I_{P}}= \frac{N_{P}}{N_{S}}

